Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Remove the @Puff Pastry Sheet{1%pack} from your fridge and allow to come up to
room temperature.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Roughly
chop the @dill{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Drain the @Fish Pie Mix{1%pack} and pat dry with kitchen paper.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir in the @butter{30%g} and allow to melt.

Stir in the @Plain Flour{2%tbsp} and cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes}
- you've made a roux!

Stir the @Water for the Sauce{250%ml} into the roux a little at a time until
combined. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{75%g}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{15%g},
@Wholegrain Mustard{17%g} and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g}. Bring to the
boil, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Stir the fish pie mix, @peas{120%g} and dill through the sauce until combined,
then transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Cover with the pastry, pressing it over the side of the dish or just sitting it
on top, then trimming off any excess. Make a small hole in the middle to allow
steam to escape.

> TIP: Brush the pastry with a little milk if you have some.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{15-20%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

== Garlicky Green Beans ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated or minced). Trim
the @Green Beans{150%g}(trimmed).

Clean out the (now empty) frying pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle
of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Stir in the garlic, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of @water{1%splash} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some
#foil{}. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from the heat and cover to
keep warm.

== To Serve ==

Share the fish pie between your plates.

Serve with the garlicky green beans alongside.

Enjoy!